review: The course was very useful. I learned how to build websites using HTML, CSS, and JavaScript. We also used PHP and MySQL for server-side coding.
Interesting course that covered data structures. The projects were helpful but challenging. The professor was supportive and explained well.
The course covered networking basics and protocols. Some parts were a bit fast, but overall good. Assignments helped reinforce the concepts.
Excellent course on software engineering principles. Loved the team project and agile methodology sessions.
Good introduction to networking. Labs were very practical and enjoyable. Needed more real-world examples though.
Basic computer engineering concepts. Some lectures were a bit dry but projects were fun and hands-on.
Information systems course with lots of practical case studies. Learned a lot about database management systems.
The content was difficult to follow at times. More examples in lectures would have helped.
Advanced software engineering topics were covered. The final project was challenging but rewarding.
Loved the course on enterprise systems. The ERP simulation was one of the best activities we did.
